.TH DBX-CONTAINERS 1 "2026-06-20" "dbx 0.36.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-containers \- manage the dbx auto-managed Docker containers as a group
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx containers
.RB [ list | restart | start | stop | down ]
.RB [ \-y ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
dbx restores into auto-managed local containers
.RB ( postgres-dbx ", " mysql-dbx ,
or the names set by
.B DBX_POSTGRES_CONTAINER
/
.BR DBX_MYSQL_CONTAINER ),
which it labels
.BR com.dbx.managed=true .
.B dbx containers
lets you see and control that group without raw
.BR docker
commands. The managed set is the union of the known names and every container
carrying the
.B com.dbx.managed
label.
.SH ACTIONS
.TP
.B list
(default) Show each managed container with its status and image.
.TP
.B restart
Restart the managed containers. Restored databases inside them are preserved.
.TP
.B start
Start any stopped managed containers.
.TP
.B stop
Stop the running managed containers.
.TP
.B down " [" \-y ]
Remove the managed containers. This destroys any restored databases inside
them; on-disk backups under
.B $DBX_DATA_DIR
are unaffected. Prompts for confirmation unless
.B \-y
(or
.BR \-\-yes )
is given.
.SH NOTES
A stopped managed container is also started automatically the next time a dbx
command needs it, so an explicit
.B start
is rarely required.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR dbx-restore (1)
